# .trivyignore — repository-wide Trivy suppression list.
#
# Each line is a single CVE or advisory ID that Trivy should skip. Every
# entry MUST carry a short rationale so a future reader can re-audit the
# decision. When a suppression is no longer needed (fix available and
# applied), delete the entry.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# CVE-2026-33671 — picomatch <4.0.4 (Regular Expression Denial of Service
# via crafted extglob patterns). Reachable only from `picomatch` bundled
# inside npm's own `node_modules/npm/node_modules/picomatch` which ships
# with the `node:22-alpine` base image. We do NOT execute npm at runtime
# — the container entrypoint is `node dist/index.js` — so the vulnerable
# code path is never loaded. Our own prod deps do not depend on
# picomatch at all (`npm ls picomatch --omit=dev` returns empty). This
# entry should be removed once the upstream `node:22-alpine` image ships
# with npm bundling picomatch >= 4.0.4.
CVE-2026-33671
